<taxonomicName LSID="50600C4A-E38B-5261-9648-F3028DEF1DD6" authority="Faber, 1967" authorityName="Faber" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius reginae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reginae">Lasius reginae Faber, 1967</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: Slavyanka Mt., Goleshovo vill., 16.08.2014, 20 w. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F7727185" captionText="Figure 8. Lasius reginae, worker lateral: specimen from Goleshovo vill.; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653860" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">8</figureCitation>
) in a nest of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius alienus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alienus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Lasius alienus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="FÃ¶rster">Foerster</normalizedToken>
, 1850) located at the side of a path along the edge of a forest. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. This is a very rarely recorded temporary social parasite of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Foerster" baseAuthorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius alienus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alienus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Lasius alienus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from several European countries, as well as from Turkey and Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation author="Aibek, U." journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="197 - 202" refId="B7725579" refString="Aibek, U., Yamane, S., 2010. Discovery of the subgenera Austrolasius and Dendrolasius of the ant genus Lasius (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Mongolia. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology 16 (2): 197 - 202" title="Discovery of the subgenera Austrolasius and Dendrolasius of the ant genus Lasius (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Mongolia" volume="16" year="2010">Aibek and Yamane 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Borowiec, L." journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 340" refId="B7725633" refString="Borowiec, L., 2014. Catalogue of ants of Europe, the Mediterranean Basin and adjacent regions (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Genus 25 (1-2): 1 - 340" title="Catalogue of ants of Europe, the Mediterranean Basin and adjacent regions (Hymenoptera: Formicidae)" volume="25" year="2014">Borowiec 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faber" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lasius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasius reginae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reginae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Lasius reginae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
joins 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. carniolicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="carniolicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">L. carniolicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mayr, 1861 as the second member of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Austrolasius" genus="L." lsidName="(Austrolasius) subsp. subgenus" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="subGenus" species="carniolicus" subGenus="Austrolasius" subSpecies="subgenus">subgenus Austrolasius</taxonomicName>
known from Bulgaria. It differs from the latter in a reduced chaetotaxy (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F7727185" captionText="Figure 8. Lasius reginae, worker lateral: specimen from Goleshovo vill.; scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e83658.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/653860" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
